April 2025 County of Marin EMS O 2
IMMINENT DELIVERY (NORMAL)
Indications
Imminent delivery as indicated by regular contractions, bloody show, low back pain, need to
bear down, presence of crowning
ALS RMC
• Provide reassurance and instructions during delivery
• Contact hospital
• If infant is < 36 weeks gestation, prepare for
neonatal resuscitation and early transport
Start IV; NS TKO if time allows prior to delivery
During Delivery
• As head is delivered, gently wipe baby’s mouth and nose keeping head dependent
• If the cord is around neck and can’t be slipped over the head: Double clamp and
cut between clamps
After Delivery
• Allow delivery, dry baby and keep warm
• Place baby on mother’s abdomen or breast
• Delay cord clamping until 30-60 seconds after birth,
then clamp and cut 6-8 inches from baby
• Apgar score at 1 and 5 minutes
• Allow delivery of placenta, save and bring to hospital
APGAR SCORE
Sign 0 1 2
Pink body with blue
Appearance Blue or pale Completely pink
extremities
Pulse Absent <100/minute >/= 100/minute
Grimace No response Grimacing/weak cry Vigorous cry
Activity Limp Some flexion Active movement
Respirations Absent Slow, irregular Good, crying
